        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-05-16T18:02:45Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Since glibc uses the __ptrace_request enum instead of #defining macros, we should try to maintain equivalence by using a constexpr variable instead of a macro.\n\nstatic constexpr __ptrace_request PTRACE_ARCH_PRCTL \u003d static_cast\u003c__ptrace_request\u003e(30);",
      "revId": "dd0b2446a7df246e97ab204494b6891ed6eb7f89",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "6eaabf95_53e58cb6",
        "filename": "compat/linux/sys/ptrace.h",
        "patchSetId": 21
      },
      "lineNbr": 22,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-05-16T18:02:45Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "But the fact remains that the kernel’s arch/x86/include/uapi/asm/ptrace-abi.h only defines this value for __x86_64__, and the kernel will only do anything with it when passed by an x86_64 user process.\n\nYou’ve established that we do need this file to make PTRACE_ARCH_PRCTL available under glibc, but I still think that we should restrict it to only be available on __x86_64__.",
      "revId": "dd0b2446a7df246e97ab204494b6891ed6eb7f89",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
